comment: Brown (BOS) and Mirotic (CHI) briefly engage and separate during rebounding.
Wade (CHI) makes body contact with Crowder (BOS) and affects his SQBR on the drive to the basket.
Gibson (CHI) makes marginal contact with Bradley (BOS) on the screen.
Mirotic (CHI) makes marginal contact with Thomas (BOS) that does not affect his SQBR.
Thomas (BOS) does not have part of his hand under the ball when he brings it to a pause and continues his dribble.
Crowder (BOS) dislodges Butler (CHI), affecting his ability to retrieve the rebound.
Gibson (CHI) is not in a vertical position and makes arm contact with Horford (BOS) that affects his driving shot attempt.
Bradley's (BOS) jumps from point A to point B and makes contact with Wade (CHI) that affects his shooting motion.
[Observable in enhanced video] Traveling is called, but enhanced video review shows that Brown (BOS) releases the ball just before his foot touches the floor.
Crowder (BOS) makes contact with the ball without affecting Butler's (CHI) drive to the basket.
Thomas (BOS) pivots backwards into Butler (CHI) and does not give him room to avoid the screen.
Wade (CHI) makes contact with the ball without affecting Green's (BOS) shooting motion.
Johnson (BOS) makes contact with Butler (CHI) that affects his SQBR.
